properties.areaDesc: San Diego County Mountains; Riverside County Mountains
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 9 at 8:19PM PST until February 11 at 4:00AM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow expected. Plan on slippery road conditions,
including during the morning commute on Monday. Total snow
accumulations of up to 3 inches, with localized amounts up to 10
inches, are expected.

* WHERE...The Mountains of Riverside and San Diego Counties.

* WHEN...10 PM today to 4 AM Tuesday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Be prepared for reduced visibility at
times.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for snow means periods of snow will
cause primarily travel difficulties. Be prepared for snow covered
roads and limited visibility, and use caution while driving.

For road condition information in California...enter
8 0 0 4 2 7 7 6 2 3 if inside california or
9 1 6 4 5 5 7 6 2 3 if outside California.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM PST TUESDAY ABOVE 4000 FEET
